        {
          "id": "chapter-1-arrival",
          "title": "Roots in the Square",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Mara braces the cracked roofs, then maps the root's pulse from beam to beam across the village. Its movement is not an attack but a trapped creature searching for the path it once knew.",
            "Fear and dry thunder shape the root tip into the Rootquake Hart, which bucks beneath the square whenever the villagers pull against it. Mara must ease each brace in sequence and guide the frightened manifestation toward open ground."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Mara steadies timber braces around a great root shaped like an antlered hart beneath the village square.",
          "actionLabel": "Settle the root"
        }
      ]
    },
