          "title": "The Cloud Garden",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Beyond the gates, walking trees cradle pearl-gray clouds inside immense root chambers. Their glass-winged pollinators are alive but scattered, unable to cross the broken warm-air paths that once joined flower to flower.",
            "Confused flight lines harden into the Shardwing Murmuration, a dazzling flock that drives every pollinator away from the cloud blooms. Mara repairs the thermal wheels while Orra guides the swarm into its old living pattern."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Glass-winged insects spiral around luminous cloud blossoms as Mara repairs a mossy wind wheel.",
          "actionLabel": "Mend the flight paths"
        }
      ]
