          "id": "chapter-6-arrival",
          "title": "The Captive Tree",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Commissioner Senn diverts the final rain tree into a deep holding basin, convinced that one captive source can guarantee water for the greatest number. Mara follows its distress through severed roots while Iven sees his own old logic magnified in Senn's plan.",
            "The capture basin drinks without filling and becomes the Bottomless Cistern, an abyssal hunger that pulls cloud, root, and river into itself. Mara reconnects the tree's buried signals so every threatened watershed can answer its call."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "A walking rain tree strains above a black bottomless cistern while green root signals spread through the earth.",
          "actionLabel": "Answer the captive tree"
        }
      ]
    },
