          "title": "A Living Channel",
          "paragraphs": [
            "As the wider watershed fails, Mara asks the villages to stop defending an aqueduct that can only preserve one shrinking season. Together they reshape terraces, gates, and bridges into a route where water and roots can move side by side.",
            "Discarded masonry and cut roots bind into the Oldcourse Colossus, a rootbound monument to every shortcut the valley took around living change. The community dismantles it piece by piece, reusing each stone in the new channel."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Villagers transform a tangled colossus of roots and old masonry into bridges along a green migration corridor.",
          "actionLabel": "Build the living channel"
        }
      ]
