          "id": "chapter-8-arrival",
          "title": "When the Trees Return",
          "paragraphs": [
            "The corridor opens, but the exhausted trees no longer remember how to begin their migration. Mara tunes the structures, Iven releases the gates, and Orra invites the whole valley to carry the song she once guarded alone.",
            "The forest's unspent weather blooms overhead as the Rainstar Canopy, a cosmic tangle of lightning and luminous seed paths. By opening every channel in sequence, the valley turns that dangerous pressure into rain and gives the trees a road home."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Walking trees cross the opened valley beneath a vast canopy of stars, seeds, lightning, and newborn rain.",
          "actionLabel": "Sing the forest home"
        }
      ]
