          "id": "rain-on-every-roof",
          "title": "Rain on Every Roof",
          "paragraphs": [
            "The rain trees walk beyond the valley, and storms return to watersheds that had begun to disappear. In Mara's village, water drums on repaired roofs while children follow glass-winged pollinators through the square.",
            "Senn releases control of the holding basin and helps convert it into a resting garden along the route. Iven keeps one cracked aqueduct stone above his desk as a promise that good work must remain able to change."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Warm rain falls on ochre rooftops as glass-winged pollinators and children cross a green village square.",
          "actionLabel": "Welcome the rain"
        },
        {
          "id": "the-next-migration",
          "title": "The Next Migration",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Orra teaches the full migration song in the open, adding every new verse the travelers bring back. The aqueduct and the forest now share a calendar shaped by observation instead of ownership.",
            "Mara shoulders her roof-mender's tools and follows a young root toward the next dry valley. Far below, an ancient tree takes one patient step, and a cloud begins to glow."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Mara walks beside a young green root toward distant terraces while a luminous rain tree moves beneath the hills.",
          "actionLabel": "Follow the next root",
